headline.main: Review: A Man and a Woman (and Another Woman) in ‘Lover for a Day’
headline.print_headline: A Love Triangle With Angles That Are Awkward
title: Lover for a Day
overview: After a bad breakup, a college-aged Parisian moves into her father's flat only to discover that he is living with his new girlfriend - a young woman her age.
genres: id: 18, name: Drama, id: 10749, name: Romance
spoken_languages: english_name: French, iso_639_1: fr, name: Français
production_countries: iso_3166_1: FR, name: France

abstract: This feature debut of the writer and director Francis Lee is a bracing, sometimes brutal movie.
snippet: This feature debut of the writer and director Francis Lee is a bracing, sometimes brutal movie.
lead_paragraph: Trapped between skies like beaten tin and earth scrubbed raw by wind and rain, the characters in “God’s Own Country” are well used to harshness. Like Johnny (Josh O’Connor), who labors on his struggling family farm in Yorkshire under the critical eyes of his sick father (Ian Hart) and stolid grandmother (Gemma Jones). For relief, he vents his frustrations in binge-drinking and furtive, feral sex with random young men.

abstract: Idris Elba and Kate Winslet crash into a mountain — and each other — in this drama.
snippet: Idris Elba and Kate Winslet crash into a mountain — and each other — in this drama.
lead_paragraph: To watch the magnetic Idris Elba trudge through a monumental dud like “The Mountain Between Us” is almost physically painful. Paired with an aloof Kate Winslet — with whom he has less chemistry than he did with Wood Harris, who played his business partner on “The Wire” — he works very hard to appear oblivious to the script’s many idiocies. He does not succeed.

headline.main: Review: Love in a Cold Climate in ‘The Mountain Between Us’
title: The Mountain Between Us
overview: Stranded on a mountain after a tragic plane crash, two strangers must work together to endure the extreme elements of the remote, snow-covered terrain. When they realize help is not coming, they embark on a perilous journey across hundreds of miles of wilderness, pushing each other to survive and discovering their inner strength.

abstract: A sheltered young woman enamored of the films of the famous director sets off to Italy to meet him.
snippet: A sheltered young woman enamored of the films of the famous director sets off to Italy to meet him.
lead_paragraph: Nancy Cartwright, the voice of Bart Simpson on the long-running animated television series, has made her first movie as a screenwriter and producer, a charming drama about the love of movies and youthful passion. “In Search of Fellini” reimagines a whirlwind adventure Ms. Cartwright once had to try to meet the Italian director Federico Fellini. With the help of her longtime collaborator and co-writer, Peter Kjenaas, and the first-time director Taron Lexton, Ms. Cartwright creates a Felliniesque fantasy of her own.

headline.main: Review: Love of Il Maestro Drives ‘In Search of Fellini’
title: In Search of Fellini
overview: Lucy, a small-town girl from Ohio, discovers the delightfully bizarre films of legendary filmmaker Federico Fellini and sets off on a journey across Italy to find him.

abstract: In war-torn Liberia, Charlize Theron and Javier Bardem face a big problem: how to keep their knotty relationship from fizzling.
snippet: In war-torn Liberia, Charlize Theron and Javier Bardem face a big problem: how to keep their knotty relationship from fizzling.
lead_paragraph: Sean Penn has some significant experience as a human-rights activist. He has shown commendable stalwartness in walking the walk, so to speak, not just starting a foundation to help victims of  Haiti’s 2010 earthquake but traveling there to help on the ground. We can read Mr. Penn’s latest directorial effort, “The Last Face,” as a kind of tribute to the aid workers he has met. As well meaning as this movie is, it is also a turgid, muddled one.

headline.main: Review: Aid Workers in Love and War in Sean Penn’s ‘The Last Face’
title: The Last Face
overview: Miguel, a heroic Spanish doctor, puts himself in harm's way to deliver medical treatment to the victims of military uprisings in Africa.
genres: id: 18, name: Drama
spoken_languages: english_name: English, iso_639_1: en, name: English, english_name: Portuguese, iso_639_1: pt, name: Português
production_countries: iso_3166_1: US, name: United States of America

abstract: The filmmakers Fiona Gordon and Dominique Abel star in their fourth movie, a tale infused with physical comedy about a woman in search of her aunt.
snippet: The filmmakers Fiona Gordon and Dominique Abel star in their fourth movie, a tale infused with physical comedy about a woman in search of her aunt.
lead_paragraph: In “Lost in Paris,” the married directors and stars Fiona Gordon and Dominique Abel show a grace for physical comedy and pretzel-like pas de deux. If their fourth feature (their first three, including “L’Iceberg” and “The Fairy,” were directed with Bruno Romy) is mild by design, their style — equal parts Jacques Tati, Jerry Lewis, Wes Anderson and “Wallace & Gromit” — isn’t easy to pull off.

abstract: This moody romance stars Tatiana Maslany (“Orphan Black”) as a bipolar painter in love with a brooding cabby (Tom Cullen of “Downton Abbey”).
snippet: This moody romance stars Tatiana Maslany (“Orphan Black”) as a bipolar painter in love with a brooding cabby (Tom Cullen of “Downton Abbey”).
lead_paragraph: Acting prowess is in vast abundance in the moody romance “The Other Half.” Tatiana Maslany (the dazzling star of “Orphan Black”) plays Emily, a bipolar painter and teacher; Tom Cullen (Lord Gillingham on “Downton Abbey”) portrays Nickie, a brooding cabdriver and musician whose brother vanished almost five years ago. When these two meet, passionate sparks fly, but not without consequences.

abstract: A nurse travels to the Ottoman Empire on the eve of World War I. Can romance blossom amid earthshaking events?
snippet: A nurse travels to the Ottoman Empire on the eve of World War I. Can romance blossom amid earthshaking events?
lead_paragraph: “The Ottoman Lieutenant” is an overwrought nurse romance merged with a history lesson, a combination that is hard to take as seriously as the film wants to be taken.

headline.main: Review: Love as the World Wars, in ‘The Ottoman Lieutenant’
headline.print_headline: Review: Love as the World Wars, in ‘The Ottoman Lieutenant’
title: The Ottoman Lieutenant
overview: Lillie, a determined American woman, ventures overseas to join Dr. Jude at a remote medical mission in the Ottoman Empire (now Turkey). However, Lillie soon finds herself at odds with Jude and the mission’s founder, Woodruff, when she falls for the titular military man, Ismail, just as the war is about to erupt.

abstract: Josh Kornbluth runs afoul of the Internal Revenue Service after failing to file tax returns for seven years.
snippet: Josh Kornbluth runs afoul of the Internal Revenue Service after failing to file tax returns for seven years.
lead_paragraph: Likability goes a long way in “Love & Taxes,” a comedy that relies on the friendly style of its star to carry a rambling story. If there aren’t many big laughs here, there are enough smiles to make the time pass pleasantly enough.

headline.main: Review: It’s All Mirth and Taxes in ‘Love & Taxes’
title: Love & Taxes
overview: She’s a young pianist preparing for an audition. He is a games inventor who can only concentrate in complete silence. Separated by only a paper-thin wall in conjoined apartments, will they learn to live in harmony with one another? Will romance blossom through the wall?
